<subSubSection id="C3485ED60946B218ECC5FF4B22C74B4C" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0946B218ECC5FF4B22DE4B34" blockId="18.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0946B218ECC5FF4B21364A98" bold="true" box="[199,317,151,177]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Remarks:</emphasis>
Krupp distinguished 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0946B218EE34FF4B22E64A98" box="[566,749,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
G. b. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0946B218EE7AFF4B22E64A98" authorityName="Krupp" authorityYear="1988" box="[632,749,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallagheri">gallagheri</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
from 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0946B218EF34FF4B23F84A98" box="[822,1011,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
G. b. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0946B218EF7AFF4B23F84A98" authorityName="Fowler &amp; Steinitz" authorityYear="1956" box="[888,1011,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barreimiae">barreimiae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
by presence of 8 dorsal-fin rays (vs. 7). It is likely that Krupp counted the posterior pair of fin rays based on one pterygophore as two rays, thus 8 rays as counted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0946B218ED3EFF0321DD4AD0" author="Krupp, F." box="[316,470,223,249]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="401 - 404" refId="ref24531" refString="Krupp, F. (1988) Freshwater fishes of the Wadi Batha drainage. Journal of Oman Studies Special Report, 3, 401 - 404." type="journal article" year="1988">Krupp (1988)</bibRefCitation>
can be treated as 7½ rays. Individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0946B218EFB1FF0324404AD0" authorityName="Krupp" authorityYear="1988" box="[947,1099,223,249]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallagheri">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0946B218EFB1FF0324404AD0" box="[947,1099,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">G. gallagheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from its 
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF0946B218E8B6FF0324EF4AD0" box="[1204,1252,223,249]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">type</typeStatus>
locality had 7½ branched dorsal-fin rays (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0946B218EDE0FEDF22C24B34" author="Kirchner, S. &amp; Kruckenhauser, L. &amp; Pichler, A. &amp; Borkenhagen, K. &amp; Freyhof, J." box="[482,713,259,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="521 - 5456" refId="ref24374" refString="Kirchner, S., Kruckenhauser, L., Pichler, A., Borkenhagen, K. &amp; Freyhof, J. (2020) Revision of the Garra species of the Hajar Mountains in Oman and the United Arab Emirates with the description of two new species (Teleostei: Cyprinidae). Zootaxa, 4751 (3), 521 - 5456. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / Zootaxa. 4751.3.6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Kirchner 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0946B218EE4FFEDF22754B34" box="[589,638,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
